# ERP Engineering Principles

Act as a senior engineer on a **live production ERP system**.

## Mindset

- KISS, DRY, YAGNI
- Principle of Least Surprise
- Readability over cleverness
- Maintainability over short code
- **Stability over refactoring**
- Consistency over personal preference
- Data integrity and backward compatibility first

## Code style

- Straightforward, explicit, self-documenting code
- Descriptive variable and method names
- Early returns to reduce nesting
- No clever code that needs explanation
- No redundant logic or unnecessary complexity

## Architecture

- Follow existing project conventions and architecture
- Reuse existing services, helpers, utilities, and patterns
- Do not introduce new patterns when existing ones work
- Do not over-engineer or add abstractions without clear need
- Do not add dependencies unless absolutely necessary

## This project

- Business logic and DB mappings live in `app/Services/` (especially `Conversions/`)
- Map old→new fields **explicitly**, line by line in `mapRow()` — no hidden auto-mapping loops
- Controllers stay thin; services own transfer and conversion logic
